method.description:
Returns an array of dictionaries representing the current call stack. [codeblock] func _ready(): foo()
func foo(): bar()
func bar(): print(get_stack()) [/codeblock] would print [codeblock] [{function:bar, line:12, source:res://script.gd}, {function:foo, line:9, source:res://script.gd}, {function:_ready, line:6, source:res://script.gd}] [/codeblock] [b]Note:[/b] Not supported for calling from threads. Instead, this will return an empty array.
